reports/codex_tool_reports/dec_v61_053_round1.log:7360:  HIGH-1 · Extractor trims by sample count, not physical time. [src/cylinder_centerline_extractor.py](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/src/cylinder_centerline_extractor.py:140) uses `int(n_total * window_start_fraction)`, while the FO writes with `writeControl timeStep` and adjustable `deltaT` in [src/foam_agent_adapter.py](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/src/foam_agent_adapter.py:4895). Early small timesteps can overpopulate startup samples, so “0.5” may not mean “after t=100s”. `min_samples=4` can also pass a physically tiny window. Suggested fix: trim by time threshold `t_min + fraction*(t_max-t_min)` and require a minimum physical duration or shedding-cycle count.
